More than two thirds (67 per cent) of respondents said they were more adventurous in the bedroom than their other half.

These respondents were asked to share their exploits, in terms of the things they had tried in the past.

The top five most popular antics of sexually ‘adventurous’ Britons were role play (72 per cent), sex outdoors (61 per cent), sex in public places (37 per cent), sex with a stranger (28 per cent), and threesomes (26 per cent).

Less than half of the respondents (47 per cent) stated that they had embarked upon these experiences with their current partner.

Instead, the most common accomplice was ‘an ex-partner’ (64 per cent), followed by ‘a friend with benefits’ (28 per cent).

