When asked if they ever felt ‘frustrated’ with their current partner’s sexual preferences, a quarter (23 per cent) confirmed they did.

The top three issues amongst frustrated Britons in relationships were voted as ‘my partner is not adventurous enough’ (73 per cent), ‘my partner doesn’t want to have sex as often as I do’ (63 per cent) and ‘my partner wants to have sex too often’ (31 per cent).

One in ten respondents (11 per cent) confessed that they were no longer sexually attracted to their partner.

